    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="497"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.6176/134: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Swenson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 12, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Within your discretion, please see Colijn upon his return from London and
                    ascertain state of discussion regarding rubber agreement. Department will be
                    interested to know whether its suggestions receive consideration in the London
                    discussions.</p>
                <p>Referring to your despatch No. 879 of January 26,<note n="12" xml:id="d497fn12"
                        >Not printed.</note> it seems to the Department that there is no possible
                    way in which Section (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>) of the London Conference
                    resolution could be assured of effectiveness except by giving consuming
                    countries representation on the International Committee. You are authorized to
                    repeat that to Colijn.</p>
                <p>Would you kindly advise Department by telegraph what is the significance under
                    the agreement of the price which Colijn keeps emphasizing. In what sense is it a
                    pivotal price?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
